# Documentation rule

Docs are project memory.

Use these roles:

- `README.md`: public entry point.
- `ARCHITECTURE.md`: durable architecture.
- `PLAN.md`: current phase and next work.
- `AGENTS.md`: compact AI agent context.
- `docs/PROJECT_STRATEGY.md`: product strategy.
- `docs/DEVELOPMENT_STRATEGY.md`: engineering strategy.
- `docs/ROADMAP.md`: completed and future phases.
- `docs/FUTURE_FEATURES.md`: retained backlog.
- `docs/AI_COENGINEERING.md`: ChatGPT and Cursor workflow.
- specs: contracts and invariants.
- historical docs: completed execution criteria.

When moving or renaming docs, update links.

When a feature is deferred, preserve it in `docs/FUTURE_FEATURES.md` if it remains desirable.

Mark historical execution docs clearly rather than letting them look like active plans.

When a shipped vertical slice changes product behavior (e.g. overlay readability presentation or **new / renamed `scene.overlayReadability.perLayer` keys** beyond the six shipped defaults — `grid`, `solarAnalemma`, `subsolarMarker`, `sublunarMarker`, `cityPins`, `staticEquirectOverlay` per [`src/config/v2/sceneConfig.ts`](src/config/v2/sceneConfig.ts); or **new / renamed base-map `capabilities`** that affect upstream overlay lift such as `reliefShaded` / `boundaryDense` / `chromaticDense`; or **meaningful upstream planetary illumination / twilight sampling changes** documented as a phase in `PLAN.md`), sync `README.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md` maturity, `PLAN.md`, `docs/ROADMAP.md`, `docs/FUTURE_FEATURES.md`, `docs/PROJECT_STRATEGY.md`, `docs/AI_COENGINEERING.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `docs/DEVELOPMENT_STRATEGY.md` so “shipped vs future” stays obvious without reading source.
